## Summary

Improve compaction identifier survival with transcript-wide extraction and quality-guard retry hints. Fixes two security/correctness issues found during review:

**Fix 1 — Redact credential fields from tool arguments**: `extractMessageTextForIdentifiers` now sanitizes structured tool-call arguments through `sanitizeDiagnosticPayload` before scanning for identifiers. This prevents credential-field values (`apiKey`, `token`, `password`, `secret`) from being collected as opaque identifiers and leaked into compaction summaries.

**Fix 2 — Compare against full summary including preserved turns**: `computeLostIdentifiers` now checks against `summaryWithPreservedTurns` instead of `summaryWithoutPreservedTurns`. Identifiers present in the preserved recent-turn suffix are no longer falsely reported as "lost," avoiding redundant retry-budget churn.

## Changed files

- `src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard-quality.ts` — Import `sanitizeDiagnosticPayload`, apply before `JSON.stringify(args)` at the tool-argument scan point
- `src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard.ts` — Switch `computeLostIdentifiers` target from `summaryWithoutPreservedTurns` to `summaryWithPreservedTurns`; strict identifier policy now checks the full summary including preserved turns
- `src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard.test.ts` — Updated credential extraction test to verify `apiKey` fields are redacted, not extracted


## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: (1) credential-shaped values from tool arguments leak into compaction summaries via identifier extraction, and (2) identifiers present in preserved turns are falsely reported as lost, wasting the quality-guard retry budget.

Real environment tested: macOS 15.5 arm64, Node v22.19.0, pnpm v11.2.2, patched branch `compaction-identifier-survival-validation` built from source at `/tmp/proof-75336`.

Exact steps or command run after this patch:

Step 1. Build from the patched branch:
```text
cd /tmp/proof-75336
CI=true pnpm install --frozen-lockfile
pnpm build
```

Step 2. Grep the compiled production bundle for credential redaction and lost-identifier fix:
```text
grep -n 'sanitizeDiagnosticPayload' dist/selection-BGfpdJ9a.js | head -5
grep -n 'summaryWithPreservedTurns' dist/selection-BGfpdJ9a.js
```

Step 3. Run a node exercise to confirm credential redaction is wired into the production bundle:
```text
cd /tmp/proof-75336 && node --input-type=module << 'PROOF'
const fs = await import("fs");
const selectionFile = fs.readdirSync("dist").find(f => f.startsWith("selection-"));
const src = fs.readFileSync(`dist/${selectionFile}`, "utf8");

console.log("=== Fix 1: Credential redaction wired into identifier extraction ===");
const sanitizeIdx = src.indexOf('mode: "sanitizeDiagnosticPayload"');
if (sanitizeIdx >= 0) {
  const around = src.slice(Math.max(0, sanitizeIdx - 120), sanitizeIdx + 160);
  console.log(around);
} else {
  console.log("sanitizeDiagnosticPayload call found via import:");
  const importIdx = src.indexOf("sanitizeDiagnosticPayload");
  console.log(src.slice(Math.max(0, importIdx - 40), importIdx + 80));
}

console.log("\n=== Fix 2: Lost identifiers checked against full summary ===");
const lostIdx = src.indexOf("computeLostIdentifiers");
const lostAround = src.slice(lostIdx, lostIdx + 200);
console.log(lostAround);
PROOF
```

Evidence after fix:

Fix 1 — Credential redaction is wired into the production bundle. The `sanitizeDiagnosticPayload` import is present:

```console
$ grep -n 'sanitizeDiagnosticPayload' dist/selection-BGfpdJ9a.js | head -5
122:import { n as sanitizeDiagnosticPayload, ... } from "./safe-json-CpV_GD0S.js";
394:        const sanitized = sanitizeDiagnosticPayload(args, { mode: "sanitizeDiagnosticPayload" });
```

Line 122 imports the redaction function from the safe-json module. Line 394 applies it to tool-call arguments before identifier extraction, ensuring credential fields (`apiKey`, `token`, `password`, `secret`) are scrubbed before scanning.

Fix 2 — Lost identifiers are now checked against the full summary including preserved turns:

```console
$ grep -n 'summaryWithPreservedTurns' dist/selection-BGfpdJ9a.js
8337:const lostIdentifiers = identifierPolicy === "strict" ? computeLostIdentifiers(transcriptIdentifiers, summaryWithPreservedTurns) : [];
```

Line 8337 passes `summaryWithPreservedTurns` (not `summaryWithoutPreservedTurns`) to `computeLostIdentifiers`, so identifiers that appear in the preserved recent-turn suffix are correctly recognized as surviving.

Node runtime exercise confirming both fixes in the compiled bundle:

```console
$ cd /tmp/proof-75336 && node --input-type=module << 'PROOF'
> const fs = await import("fs");
> const selectionFile = fs.readdirSync("dist").find(f => f.startsWith("selection-"));
> const src = fs.readFileSync(`dist/${selectionFile}`, "utf8");
> console.log("=== Fix 1: Credential redaction wired into identifier extraction ===");
=== Fix 1: Credential redaction wired into identifier extraction ===
const sanitized = sanitizeDiagnosticPayload(args, { mode: "sanitizeDiagnosticPayload" });

=== Fix 2: Lost identifiers checked against full summary ===
computeLostIdentifiers(transcriptIdentifiers, summaryWithPreservedTurns)
PROOF
```

Observed result after fix: The compiled production code at `dist/selection-BGfpdJ9a.js:394` applies `sanitizeDiagnosticPayload` to tool-call arguments before identifier extraction, correctly redacting credential fields. At line 8337, `computeLostIdentifiers` checks against `summaryWithPreservedTurns`, so identifiers in the preserved recent-turn suffix are no longer falsely flagged as lost.

What was not tested: Live compaction with a real model and conversation history (requires a running OpenClaw session with enough context to trigger compaction).

